cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use, build upon, or reference this framework in academic literature, please cite it as follows."
authors:
  - name: "Immortality Index"
    website: "https://immortality-index.pages.dev"
title: "Immortality Index: A Binary Milestone Registry for Longevity Research"
version: "1.0.0"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.PLACEHOLDER"
date-released: 2026-06-18
url: "https://github.com/immortalityindex/immortality-index"
license: CC-BY-4.0
abstract: >
  The Immortality Index is an open, version-controlled, binary milestone
  registry that operationalises the engineering prerequisites for negligible somatic senescence.
  It decomposes the biological aging problem into 24 falsifiable research obstacles across two
  primary engineering tracks — somatic genetic fidelity (Track 01) and nanoscale biomedical
  systems (Track 02) — each governed by four binary milestone gates. Milestone status is
  updated autonomously via large-language-model literature scanning against peer-reviewed
  sources. The framework is designed for formal citation, collaborative extension, and
  integration into academic longevity research programmes. This project was conceived by a
  human and developed through AI-assisted collaboration (Google Gemini, then Claude by
  Anthropic), and lightly reviewed by a human.
keywords:
  - longevity
  - biogerontology
  - negligible senescence
  - epigenetic reprogramming
  - somatic identity
  - nanotechnology
  - systems biology
  - falsifiable benchmarking
  - open science
repository-code: "https://github.com/immortalityindex/immortality-index"
